<br>
The best of these looks like it's going to be Morrowind. You'll need a beefy PC to run it, but it sounds like just the thing to tide me over until NWN. Here's one of the better written previews and I have not seen a bad word said about this game yet.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wargamer.com/reviews/morrowind_preview_main.asp">www.wargamer.com/reviews/morrowind_preview_main.asp</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
The other primo titles coming out soon are Freedom Force, a superhero based sort of Xcom type game, from the makers of System Shock and Dungeon Siege, which is sort of a Diablo clone with some similarities to RTS games. If I find good previews I will link them here as well.<br>
<br>
-Creepy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/unummies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NummieS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(3/20/02 8:55:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=988.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: OT: Morrowind</span><hr size=1> I'm very intriuged about Morrowind..... just like i was with DF and DF2 but Bethesda has been notorious for releasing ridiculously high bugged games.  Yes...  I kept playing them through all the problems but at the time there was nothing else out on the market that could match the graphics.  I loved the Ultima Underworld series and was ready for the next set of games like that.  So i endured the pain.<br>
<br>
Call me jaded but I handed them ~$110 for games that barely worked...... i still have that feeling that i ate a big @#%$ sandwich..... but I AM hoping that Bethesda views this next release as their holy grail and have put a lot of attention into making it right or this release could end up being a nice sharp headsmans axe.  <br>
<br>
I just read some information on Dungeon Siege and that looks pretty promising.... kind of like an upscale version of Warcraft in more of a D&amp;D type system.<br>
<br>
But I am really looking forward to NWN!!!!  Was really bumbed when i heard about all the legal problems they were having.  I think it would be really cool to set up some gaming sessions... maybe 1 night a week with anyone in the guild who has similar interest in this!!  <br>
<br>
This game sounds like it's going to have endless options with being able to construct your own &quot;modules.&quot;  I like their concept..... providing all the tools needed to feed the creative minds of all our inner DMs.  They are going to have people out there who will create modules that are equal in quality if not better than their own!  Now that is great strategic conceptualization by the developers.<br>
<br>
